From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 18:30:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Wire GRX-009 luminance gated dispatch bring-up opt-in

Stacked on 0001-rurix-accel-module-scaffold.patch,
0002-rurix-accel-luminance-pass-gate.patch,
0003-rurix-accel-luminance-core-callsite-wiring.patch,
0004-rurix-accel-luminance-resource-mapping-scaffold.patch, and
0005-rurix-accel-luminance-runtime-binding-preflight.patch. This segment 4b
patch is gated dispatch bring-up wiring only. It keeps the pass default
disabled and fallback-first: the native Godot luminance path stays active and
the bridge still returns RXGD_STATUS_FALLBACK for RXGD_PASS_LUMINANCE_REDUCTION.

- A new per-pass opt-in setting
  rendering/rurix_accel/passes/luminance_reduction/dispatch_bringup defaults to
  false. It is separate from the existing .../enabled setting so the gated
  dispatch bring-up path must be explicitly opted into.
- rurix_accel.h declares the reserved capability flag
  RXGD_CAP_LUMINANCE_DISPATCH_BRINGUP (1u << 1) carried in RxGdCaps.flags. This
  reuses the existing flags field: the C ABI struct layout and RXGD_ABI_VERSION
  are unchanged.
- try_create_session() sets RXGD_CAP_LUMINANCE_DISPATCH_BRINGUP in caps.flags
  only when the dispatch_bringup opt-in setting is enabled. The bridge treats
  this flag as the Godot opt-in for its dispatch eligibility gate.

Even when the opt-in is enabled, this is not a real GPU pass: the bridge
dispatch bring-up gate stays closed (no linked runtime dispatch kernel and no
measured local D3D12 dispatch evidence), so rxgd_record_pass still never
returns OK for RXGD_PASS_LUMINANCE_REDUCTION, no D3D12 dispatch is recorded,
the native Godot luminance path stays active, and no visual diff, measured
telemetry, or performance claim is made.
---
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp b/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
index 1a2b3c4..2b3c4d5 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
@@ -17,7 +17,11 @@ void initialize_rurix_accel_module(ModuleInitializationLevel p_level) {
 	// GRX-009: per-pass opt-in gate; the luminance_reduction pass stays on the
 	// native Godot path unless this is explicitly enabled AND the bridge
 	// actually records the pass.
 	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/luminance_reduction/enabled", false);
+	// GRX-009 segment 4b: gated dispatch bring-up opt-in. Defaults to false so
+	// the native Godot luminance path stays active; even when enabled the bridge
+	// still falls back because no real D3D12 dispatch executes yet.
+	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/luminance_reduction/dispatch_bringup", false);
 
 #if defined(D3D12_ENABLED)
 	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/enabled")) {
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h
index 4c1bc91..5d2cd02 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h
@@ -13,5 +13,9 @@
 #define RXGD_RENDER_METHOD_FORWARD_PLUS 1u
 #define RXGD_RESOURCE_TEXTURE 1u
 #define RXGD_PASS_LUMINANCE_REDUCTION 4u
+// GRX-009 segment 4b reserved capability flag carried in RxGdCaps.flags
+// (ABI v1, no struct layout change). Set only when the Godot dispatch
+// bring-up opt-in setting is enabled.
+#define RXGD_CAP_LUMINANCE_DISPATCH_BRINGUP 2u
 
 typedef struct RxGdCaps {
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
index 9b693ac..a1b2c3d 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
@@ -183,6 +183,13 @@ void RurixAccelD3D12Hooks::try_create_session() {
 	caps.struct_size = sizeof(RxGdCaps);
 	caps.backend = RXGD_BACKEND_D3D12;
 	caps.render_method = RXGD_RENDER_METHOD_FORWARD_PLUS;
+	// GRX-009 segment 4b: advertise the reserved gated dispatch bring-up opt-in
+	// flag only when the Godot per-pass setting is enabled. Even then the bridge
+	// still returns RXGD_STATUS_FALLBACK and no D3D12 dispatch is recorded.
+	// The flag defaults off and the native Godot luminance path stays active.
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/luminance_reduction/dispatch_bringup")) {
+		caps.flags |= RXGD_CAP_LUMINANCE_DISPATCH_BRINGUP;
+	}
 	if (adapter_luid_valid) {
 		memcpy(caps.adapter_luid, &adapter_luid, sizeof(adapter_luid));
 	}
